detail.title: [Parameter Change] Fix Inflation rate to 7%.
detail.description:
This is a parameter change proposal to fix inflation rate to 7%.

As #69 said, there will have a series of proposals incoming to improve the tokenomics of LikeCoin, and this is one of them.

# Before & After

## Current

- InflationMax: 10%
- InflationMin: 7%

## Proposed

- InflationMax: 7%
- InflationMin: 7%

# What does this change mean?

Long time ago, there was a passed proposal which its original goal of dynamic inflation parameter is to acheive 7% stable inflation rate if we reach 66.7% bonding, and use 20% inflation to attract delegators when the bounded rate is less than 66.7%.

However, now we have almost ~72% bonding rate, but the inflation is still 9.24%.

So, with the new parameters, we limit the maximum inflation rate to 7% to reflect the bonded ratio of LIKE.

detail.title: Creation of a new LIKE/USDC pool in Osmosis
detail.description:
This signalling proposal aims to create a new LIKE/USDC pool on Osmosis.

Pools of LIKE paired with stablecoin can reflect more accurate value of LIKE in pricing compared with current LIKE pools such as LIKE/OSMO and better protect price of LIKE from deterioration caused by the sentiment of crypto market. As native USDC now landed in Osmosis, it is benefit to LIKE stakeholders and the community to create a LIKE/USDC pool.

The cost of creation of the pool is 1000 OSMO before transaction and gas fee.

If this proposal is passed, 25000 NUM will be sent from community treasury to ERC-20 wallet 0x5eC27AF713186946ab55271427099f2d2e312390. All NUM in 0x5eC27AF713186946ab55271427099f2d2e312390 received, after transaction fees, will be converted to OSMO to create the LIKE/USDC pool on Osmosis. All remaining OSMO will be converted to LIKE and sent to the community pool.

detail.title: [Parameter Change] Update Inflation parameters.
detail.description:
（中文說明在後面）

This is a parameter change proposal to update inflation parameters.

Please go to https://dao.like.co/proposals/69 to vote.

Also, please vote the previous proposal (#67, #68) for NO because the parameter was wrong (We are not intented to change InflationMin)

# Before & After

## Current

- InflationMax: 20%
- InflationMin: 7%
- InflationRateChange: 100%
- GoalBonded: 67%

## Proposed

- InflationMax: 10%
- InflationMin: 7%
- InflationRateChange: 100% (already maximum)- GoalBonded: 66.6666666666666667%

# What does this change mean?

Long time ago, there was a passed proposal which its original goal of dynamic inflation parameter is to acheive 7% stable inflation rate if we reach 66.7% bonding, and use 20% inflation to attract delegators when the bounded rate is less than 66.7%.

However, now we have almost ~69% bonding rate, but the inflation is still near 20%.

Why? That is because the formular: `inflationRateChangePerYear = (1 - bondedRatio/params.GoalBonded) * params.InflationRateChange`, the current `inflationRateChangePerYear` is -3% for now, quite slow, which means we need 4.6 years to acheieve 7% inflation rate.

So, with the new parameters, we limit the maximum inflation rate to 10% to accommodate the current market situation right after this proposal passed.

There will have a series of proposals incoming to improve the tokenomics of LikeCoin, please keep a closer look and attend the discussion in the #proposal-discussion channel of our Discord server: https://discord.gg/likecoin

請到 https://dao.like.co/proposals/69 投票。

同時，因為我之前設定錯了參數，請對前一個提案 (#67, #68) 投反對 (這次提案不打算改變 InflationMin)

# Before & After

## Current

- InflationMax: 20%
- InflationMin: 7%
- InflationRateChange: 100%
- GoalBonded: 67%

## Proposed

- InflationMax: 10%
- InflationMin: 7%
- InflationRateChange: 100% (already maximum)
- GoalBonded: 66.6666666666666667%

# 這代表什麼改變？

很久以前曾經有一個議案通過，原意是如果整體質押率到達 66.7%，我們希望通漲可以穩定維持在 7%；但如果整體質押率小於 66.7%，通漲將會自動調整到 20% 來吸引 LikeCoin 持有者質押。

然而現在我們已經到了接近 69% 質押率，通漲卻仍然接近 20% 之高。

為什麼？因為動態調整公式：`inflationRateChangePerYear = (1 - bondedRatio/params.GoalBonded) * params.InflationRateChange`，目前的每年變化率是 -3%，非常的慢，也就是說我們要等 4.6 年才會降到 7% 通漲。

因此，新的參數將會把最大通漲限制在 10%，並將會在議案通過之後馬上生效。

接下來還會有其他改善代幣經濟的議案，如果有興趣請多留意並參與討論，你可以到我們的 Discord server: https://discord.gg/likecoin 當中的 #proposal-discussion 頻道討論。

detail.title: LikeCoin v4.0.0 ChungKing Upgrade
detail.description:
LikeCoin ChungKing Upgrade



By voting YES you approve that the chain to do a software upgrade [v4.0.0](https://github.com/likecoin/likecoin-chain/releases/tag/v4.0.0) on block height 9419200, which is estimated to occur on June 5th, around UTC 11:00.



## Upgrade features

- Upgrade golang to 1.19.5

- Upgrade cosmos-sdk to 0.46.12

- Upgrade ibc-go to 5.3.1

- Remove x/nft backport

- Add full_pay_to_royalty flag to sell NFT event

- Add deterministic ISCN ID when creating ISCN

- Add custom authz message in iscn and likenft module

- Add feegrant in iscn and likenft module messages



## Getting prepared for the upgrade

No state migration is expected for this upgrade. However all nodes are still recommended to have at least 16GB of memory. Not enough memory would result in corrupted data during upgrade.



Node operators are advised to use cosmovisor, please refer to the following guides for setup and upgrade procedure.



https://docs.like.co/validator/likecoin-chain-node/setup-a-node#to-existing-operators



https://docs.like.co/validator/chungking-upgrade



## Details of upgrade time

The proposal targets the upgrade proposal block to be 9419200, anticipated to be at June 5th, around UTC 11:00AM. Note that block times have high variance, so keep monitoring the time.



The upgrade is anticipated to take less than 60 minutes, during which time, there will not be any on-chain activity on the network.



In the event of an issue at upgrade time, we should coordinate via the validators channel in discord.



## SDK Upgrade

We will be upgrading to cosmos-sdk 0.46, which contains x/nft(which we already back-ported to sdk 0.45 in last version) and x/group module. Also ledger support for authz module is re-introduced. We will be also upgrading to ibc-go 5.3.1, which is the supported version containing security fix for Huckleberry.



## Fee grant and authz support

We have implement feegrant and authz support for iscn and x/likenft module, enabling better onboard and minting UX for users and more possibility for dApp use cases.

detail.title: [Parameter Change] Increase fee for x/iscn and x/likenft
detail.description:
（Traditional Chinese version comes after English version）
（中文版本在英文版本後面）

This is a parameter change proposal to increase fee for both x/iscn and x/likenft module.

Please go to https://dao.like.co/proposals/64 to vote.

# What does this change mean?

## For creators

If you only want to register ISCN: update ISCN will spend 10x more, but it will be still neglect-able (0.018 LIKE for average fee setting)
If you want to go further create your Writing NFT: creating NFT class and minting NFT will spend 2x more, but it will be still neglect-able (0.0034 LIKE and 2.8 LIKE respectively for average fee setting)

## For NFT collectors

Collectors will use 'Grant' module to buy NFT, so there will be no change. (0.002 LIKE for average fee setting)

## For community:

Those modules' fee will be collected by chain (like gas), so it will goes to validator and community pool, which makes the ecosystem more robust and healthy.

# Why this is important to the community?

ISCN and Writing NFT are real products, which is quite valuable and commendable among web3 world, however, the real products always have cost, so it is essential to keep the economy sustainable.

The current fee is almost zero, and it's better to adjust it to reflect the chain cost gradually, also, a reasonable fee structure can also help improving the demand side of $LIKE tokenomics, which is critical to our ecosystem.

As a participant, we should be aware to keep LikeCoin from becoming a public tragedy. This proposal is quite a small change, thus it should not stop the growth of our product.

As a validator, I'd like to take this chance to kickoff the awareness to review the fee consistently, and it is just a start for the community to judge if this is a good direction or not.

detail.title: Follow-up failed proposal #51 - Community-pool-spend Proposal: deposit 15,000,000 LIKE to Tech Subdao multisig wallet
detail.description:
Tech Subdao has been in operation for over 4 months and is on track. In particular, wallet prefix like1 was implemented in LaiChiKok upgrade, while NFT module was just launched with StarFerry update. Progress reports are available in monthly community calls and blog.like.co (latest: https://blog.like.co/en/tech-subdao-progress-update-2022-07-04/ ), and all the payments are transparently listed in a public Google Spreadsheet: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1oefPBR3wtTaf_uQorQYmYA-fv6kpF6uOzRtGjILnSv0/edit?usp=sharing 

With the rejection of proposal #51, although it's just a less than 1% below 40% quorum failure with most votes went to Yes, Tech Subdao respects the result and interprets it as a signal that the community was not totally happy with the proposal. At the same time, since the two major chain upgrades were just finished, and dao.like.co revamp is completing phase 1 at end of July, we've agreed with OurSky to suspend the out-sourced development work for now.

As such, the weekly dev cost of HKD 28,437.5 which equals roughly 2mil LIKE will last only till end of July. In this proposal, we have reduced the fund request from Community Pool by 25%, from 20,000,000 to 15,000,000 LIKE, for settling the outstanding payment to OurSky in July, and leaving a small reservation of potential maintainance in the future.

By voting YES to this proposal, you agree to send 15,000,000 LIKE to the Tech Subdao multisig wallet to support technical development of LikeCoin.

detail.title: LikeCoin v3.0.0 StarFerry NFT Upgrade
detail.description:
# LikeCoin StarFerry NFT Upgrade

By voting YES you approve that the chain to do a software upgrade [v3.0.0](https://github.com/likecoin/likecoin-chain/releases/tag/v3.0.0) on block height 4810000, which is estimated to occur on July 21st, around UTC 11:00AM.

## Upgrade features
- Add x/nft and x/likenft module
- NFT minting base on ISCN
- NFT marketplace on-chain API
- Upgrade cosmos-sdk to 0.45.6
- Upgrade ibc-go to 2.3.0

## Getting prepared for the upgrade
All nodes are recommended to have at least 32GB of memory plus extra swap for buffer. It can be a mixture of 16GB of RAM and 16GB+ of swap, or all 32GB of physical memory plus swap. Not enough memory would result in corrupted data during upgrade.

Node operators are advised to use cosmovisor, please refer to the following guides for setup and upgrade procedure.

https://docs.like.co/validator/likecoin-chain-node/setup-a-node#to-existing-operators

https://docs.like.co/validator/starferry-upgrade

## Details of upgrade time
The proposal targets the upgrade proposal block to be 4810000, anticipated to be at July 21st, around UTC 11:00AM. Note that block times have high variance, so keep monitoring the time.

The upgrade is anticipated to take less than 60 minutes, during which time, there will not be any on-chain activity on the network.

In the event of an issue at upgrade time, we should coordinate via the validators channel in discord.

## NFT Support
We have backport x/nft module from cosmos-sdk 0.46.0-rc1, and implemented our own x/likenft module. x/likenft will allow ISCN owners to mint simple or blind box NFTs based on their ISCNs. A simple marketplace API is also implemented, which allows dApps to implement NFT marketplace on chain. Future development of the x/NFT module and related NFT specifications might also allow us to send NFT via IBC.

https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmXXFEiqfvJ8LTHr9NKfNBaq5FxghP3hYjgmmJREhFxyLb

detail.title: LikeCoin v2.0.0 LaiChiKok Prefix Upgrade
detail.description:
# LikeCoin LaiChiKok Prefix Upgrade
 
 By voting YES you approve that the chain to do a software upgrade [v2.0.0](https://github.com/likecoin/likecoin-chain/releases/tag/v2.0.0) on block height 3692800, which is estimated to occur on May 4th, around UTC 11:00AM.
 
 ## Upgrade features
 - Prefix change to like with dual prefix support
 - Upgrade cosmos-sdk to 0.44.8
 - Upgrade ibc-go to 2.1.0
 - Add authz and feegrant module
 - Deprecation of legacy restful API
 
 ## Getting prepared for the upgrade
 All nodes will require 64GB of memory. This must consist of a minimum of 32GB of RAM, while the remaining 32GB can be swap. For best results, use 64GB of physical memory.
 
 Node operators are advised to use cosmovisor, please refer to the following guides for setup and upgrade procedure.
 
 https://docs.like.co/validator/likecoin-chain-node/setup-a-node#to-existing-operators
 
 https://docs.like.co/validator/laichikok-upgrade
 
 ## Details of upgrade time
 The proposal targets the upgrade proposal block to be 3692800, anticipated to be at May 4th, around UTC 11:00AM. Note that block times have high variance, so keep monitoring the time.
 
 The upgrade is anticipated to take approx 120 minutes, during which time, there will not be any on-chain activity on the network.
 
 In the event of an issue at upgrade time, we should coordinate via the validators channel in discord.
 
 ## Prefix change
 We are switching from 'cosmos' prefix to 'like' prefix to allow easier integration and identification of our chain in the ibc ecosystem. All chain store data, except static transaction data, would be migrated from 'cosmos' prefix to 'like' prefix. Signature signed by 'cosmos' address will still be supported by ante handler, however 'like' would be the default prefix from now on.
 
 DApp and exchanges should note that to check for historical transactions, both prefixes should be queried until we completely deprecate the 'cosmos' prefix in the future.

detail.title: Endorse a committee to manage the Creator's Fund
detail.description:
Abstract
I propose to further decentralize the management of Creators Fund, by endorsing a group of community members to be the "Creators Fund management committee", and apply for 2 million LIKE from the Community Pool as the first 6-month budget.
Full proposal

Background
"Creators Fund" is a budget from LikeCoin Ecosystem Pool.  Liker Land team has been managing the fund in the past years, based on the principle of matching with the sum of Civic Liker's donation.  The aim of the fund is rewarding creativity via LikeCoin button
As stated in proposal #22. the Ecosystem Pool has now been transferred to the Community Pool in order to further decentralize the governance mechanism.  The Creators Fund, which was a part of Ecosystem Pool, should also be governed in the same way.

Proposal
I propose to further decentralize the management of Creators Fund, by endorsing a group of community members to be the "Creators Fund management committee" for 1 year, and apply for 2 million LIKE from the Community Pool as the first 6-month budget.
Initial 7 committee members (Discord ID): edmondyu#9629, NoahLiu#9391, KenOokamiHoro#7356, Daisy#1990, leafwind#4213, anniezhang#0934,  mashbean#5293.  New committee member in the future, if any, must be endorsed my passing chain proposal.

Suggested duties of the committee include but not limited to:

- Review the monthly budget regularly
- Review the algorithm of fund distribution, outsource the implementation or execute by the committee itself.
- Manage the wallet of the fund
https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmPq8rRjTxViTHq7BXEKp5EnnDi8nsFbmExXC637Xk6qJM/

detail.title: Propose new set of rules and structure of the Community Delegation Committee
detail.description:
In order to accommodate the rapid growth of the LikeCoin chain and Liker Land, it is the time to propose a new set of rules and structure of the Community Delegation Committee. The committee is to serve the following purposes: 

- to support validators who are contributing to the community by managing community fund delegation from ecological pools 
- to counter the inflation and help secure the network
Currently there are 7 members in the committee: chairoikominer, Kcat, sixwood, Wright Fu, yasu, Philip Mak and Daisy. The proposal is to upgrade the existing team by endorsing the committee to continue their work for a year, and be responsible for improving the procedures from time to time and announce. 

In terms of governing principles: 

1. The committee members are obligated to maintain an open record of all the community funds delegated and communicate to the public regarding funds allocation policy and status. 
2. Official channel is apply-for-delegation on LikeCoin Discord 
3. Removing and reelection of a committee member within the term of a year will have to be agreed by 4 committee members within the committee, or by a governing proposal.
